    <div class="section">
      <h2> Group Blogs </h2>
      Group blogs tend to be more research focused and less personal but are often more frequently updated and usually have more frequent discussions.
      <ul>
	#for $feed in $qf.get().filter("type =", "groups")
	<li>
	  <div class="feedbox">
            <h3> <%=feed.title%> </h3>
	    <ul>
              #for $entry in feed.entries()
	      <li><a href="$entry.link"><%=entry.title%></a></li>
              #end for
	    </ul>
	  </div>
	</li>
        #end for
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2> Individual Researchers </h2>
      The majority of mathematical blogs are run by individual researchers mixing research and personal interests.
      <ul>
	#for $feed in $qf.get().filter("type =", "students")
	<li>
	  <div class="feedbox">
            <h3> <%=feed.title%> </h3>
	    <ul>
              #for $entry in feed.entries()
	      <li><a href="$entry.link"><%=entry.title%></a></li>
              #end for
	    </ul>
	  </div>
	</li>
        #end for
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2> Journalistic Writers </h2>
      More frequent in the science blogosphere journalistic blogs focus on communicating research to a wider audience.
      <ul>
	#for $feed in $qf.get().filter("type =", "journalism")
	<li>
	  <div class="feedbox">
            <h3> <%=feed.title%> </h3>
	    <ul>
              #for $entry in feed.entries()
	      <li><a href="$entry.link"><%=entry.title%></a></li>
              #end for
	    </ul>
	  </div>
	</li>
        #end for
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2> Communities </h2>
      Communities are a rich source for online discussions so we wouldn't want to miss them here.
      <ul>
	#for $feed in $qf.get().filter("type =", "community")
	<li>
	  <div class="feedbox">
            <h3> <%=feed.title%> </h3>
	    <ul>
              #for $entry in feed.entries()
	      <li><a href="$entry.link"><%=entry.title%></a></li>
              #end for
	    </ul>
	  </div>
	</li>
        #end for
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2> Institutions </h2>
      Some institutions have interesting feeds, too.
      <ul>
	#for $feed in $qf.get().filter("type =", "institution")
